WorldStage Newsonline– Gov. David Umahi of Ebonyi State, his daughter and three of his aides have recovered from COVID-19 Umahi on July 4, announced that he had tested positive to COVID-19 but will still be working from isolation. Mr Uchenna Orji, Commissioner for Information and Orientation said in a statement on Friday, noting that Umahi was full of praises to God for his healing. “The governor confirmed the development in a statement he personally signed. He also thanked Ebonyi people and Nigerians for their prayers and solidarity,” Orji said.